-- North Korea Awards Title of ‘DPRK Hero’ to Leader Kim Jong Il After Death
-- B y   S e o n j i n   C h a
-- 2011-12-29T21:25:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-29/north-korea-awards-title-of-dprk-hero-to-leader-kim-jong-il-after-death.html
North  Korea  awarded the title of
“DPRK Hero” to its late leader,  Kim Jong Il , state-controlled
Korean Central News Agency said. DPRK refers to  North Korea ’s
official name, the Democratic People’s Republic of Korea.  To contact the reporter on this story:
